JOHANNESBURG - The IFP mayor of Endumeni in KwaZulu-Natal, Siboniso Mbatha, has been granted bail in the Estcourt Magistrate's Court in KwaZulu-Natal. He and councillor Mthembeni Majola are accused of plotting to kill the Endumeni council Speaker, Bongiwe Mbatha-Makhathini. READ: KZN Mayor in the dock for Speaker murder plot Mbatha’s bail conditions include that he may not communicate directly with the Speaker. eNCA reporter, Samkele Maseko, spoke to Mbatha as he left court. eNCA